    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>cherry</strong> <strong>tomatoes</strong> to the dish with the <strong>chopped halloumi</strong>,<strong> halloumi juices</strong>, <strong>roasted garlic paste</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>red wine vinegar</strong> and <strong>half </strong>your<strong> dried oregano </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Add 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong>,<strong> pepper </strong>and<strong> sugar</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the dish in the oven, covered, for 30-35 min or until the veg is tender – this is your <strong>oven baked halloumi ratatouille</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
